\label{fig:fimportance}
\end{figure}

\begin{figure}[H]
\centering
\includegraphics[width=0.92\textwidth]{09_optimize_summary.png}
\caption{Before-versus-after optimization comparison for benchmarked query timings.}
\label{fig:optimize}
\end{figure}

\textbf{Explanation:} This page intentionally separates experimental modeling from release-safe KPI
proof. It preserves transparency by showing both model metrics and optimization outcomes without
overstating operational readiness.

\section{Conclusion}
This report provides a single-column, presentation-oriented submission artifact that combines
system diagrams and dashboard evidence with explicit interpretation. The structure is intentionally
reviewer-friendly: architecture first, then five dashboard pages, then conclusion. The same flow also
works as a live presentation script.

